- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of semiconductor-based energy-conversion interfaces, which is an emerging technology.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses technical and economic issues related to power systems without fuel, which can be considered as computational engineering and science.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may discuss software-related issues related to the control and management of power systems without fuel.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper may discuss the performance of power systems without fuel in terms of reliability, efficiency, and cost.
